parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy properly or may deploy unexpectedly.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard comes on
the airbag warning light illuminates
the airbags deploy unexpectedly
the airbags do not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall has left many vehicles without a functioning airbag system, putting occupants at risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard comes on
the airbag warning light illuminates
the airbags do not deploy in a crash
the airbag inflator housing may rupture
metal fragments may pass through the airbag cushion material.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall repair parts has left many vehicles without a functioning airbag system, putting occupants at risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard comes on
the airbag warning light illuminates
the airbags do not deploy in a crash
the dealer does not have the necessary parts to repair the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel overflow and stalling issues can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to loss of power steering and braking, as well as environmental hazards from spilled gasoline.
symptoms: Fuel spills out of the tank when filling up
fuel sprays back out of the tank after the pump clicks off
engine stalls after refueling
vehicle loses power steering and braking
and warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system malfunction can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to loss of power steering and braking, as well as environmental hazards from spilled gasoline.
symptoms: Fuel pump relay failure
EGR valve failure
fuel tank overflow
fuel spills out of the tank when filling up
engine stalls after refueling
and warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank overflow/spit back issue can cause fuel to spill out of the tank, potentially leading to fires, explosions, or injuries. It can also lead to fuel waste, damage to the vehicle, and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: Fuel spills out of the tank when filling up
gas sprays out of the filler neck
fuel overflows onto the ground and the vehicle
and gas splashes onto the person fueling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration issue can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unintentionally
often from a dead stop
and may occur when shifting into drive or when slowing down before coming to a stop.
